<p>
I've got a code-review for you. Here's the spec that the programmer
was given:
</p>

<ul class="org-ul">
<li>We have to read a tree-structure into memory.
</li>
<li>The end result will a tree of nodes.
</li>
<li>Each node can have 0 or more children.
</li>
<li>Each node has a value which is one of a few types: string, number, label, etc.
</li>

<li>Your job is to decide a file format for this tree, and write a
parser to read it in.
</li>
<li>The file-format must be human-writable.
</li>
</ul>

<p>
My guess is, already some of you are thinking XML; some of you are
shuddering at the very thought of XML; and most of us are thinking
some kind of
